# Design System Enforcement

This system ensures UI consistency across LexMastery.

It prevents design drift.

---

# Product Vision

Design system must:

- enforce visual consistency
- standardize spacing and typography
- control UI behavior patterns
- ensure accessibility compliance
- maintain brand identity

---

# Design Tokens

- spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48)
- font scale (caption → display)
- color tokens (primary, secondary, surface, error)
- radius tokens (small, medium, large)

---

# Typography Rules

- headings must follow hierarchy strictly
- no arbitrary font sizes
- consistent line height rules

---

# Layout Rules

- use grid-based spacing
- avoid manual margins
- enforce padding consistency

---

# Component Rules

- reuse components only
- no ad-hoc UI construction
- enforce design library usage

---

# Motion Rules

- transitions must be subtle
- avoid excessive animation
- use consistent easing curves

---

# AI UI Rules

- AI components must use distinct styling
- avoid mixing AI responses with static content
- ensure readability-first design

---

# Accessibility Rules

- color contrast must meet standards
- focus states required
- screen reader labels mandatory

---

# Offline Behaviour

- design system fully available offline
- no runtime dependency required

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Token validation

Component usage rules

Spacing enforcement

Integration Tests:

UI consistency checks

Theme switching validation

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating UI:

- always use design tokens
- never hardcode spacing or colors
- always follow typography scale
- never create one-off components